      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHAMPAGNES (2) was prominent from the outset last time out and finished third, beaten 7 metres, in a far better performance at this track over 2190m. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Steps up a level but she is good enough to cope. SHEZALOVER (7) impressed when successful at Geelong two runs ago then settled back and failed to finish off well enough at her latest appearance over 2200m at Ballarat, beaten 6 metres into fifth. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position. Finds a nice race and can return to winning form. RASTAMON (9) is looming as a real threat after a better effort last start, finishing second at Echuca over 2160m. ATTRACTED (11) is worth plenty of thought off a last-start win by 1.3 metres at this track over 1690m.",
